RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scansorial
<hw>Scan*so"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>Capable of climbing; <as>as, the woodpecker is a
<ex>scansorial</ex> bird</as>; adapted for climbing; <as>as, a
<ex>scansorial</ex> foot</as>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining
to the Scansores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scansorial tail</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a tail
in which the feathers are stiff and sharp at the tip, as in the
woodpeckers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scant</ent>⟦br⟧
